Xi calls for making the economy more open to the World
The economy must become more open to the world to spur its growth as President Xi said Tuesday in a speech to the group, facing the task of leadership reforms.
"China should concentrate on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop a policy of openness," he said, referring to the participants of the 16th Meeting of the Committee of the Central leading group on comprehensive deepening of reforms.
He said the expansion of openness and a deepening of reform will give the economy a new impetus and vitality and provide new space for economic development.
The leading group adopted a number of directives, including the introduction of regulation for investors to access the market, changing the rules of border controls, the promotion of state-owned enterprises (SOE), attracting private capital and review of the registration system.
According to the statement, will be compiled a list of sectors of the economy and production, unavailable for investment.
The system will be gradually debugged through pilot programs.
This is an important step, because it will give the market a bigger role in allocating resources, ensuring the rule of law in business and increasing openness, said in a statement.
The government also will weaken control of the powers granted to them to companies, thus ensuring that companies themselves will conduct their business.
The statement also says that China will allow the border regions to develop new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to strengthen local growth.
Even more areas will be available for private investors to increase openness by state-controlled sectors of the economy.
"The Government will not change its policy on foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing, as well as provide them with the best conditions," it said in a statement.
Additionally facilitate the procedure for filing applications for permanent residence permits for foreigners, or "newcomers" by optimizing requirements and simplifying the application process itself.
The meeting also discussed the provision of rights lawyers and questions of training professional judges and prosecutors.
According to an official report released after the meeting, it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang and Liu and Zhang Ministers.
